&gt; I had similar thoughts to David. My motivation was working from home 
&gt; when I didn&#39;t have access to the database but would still like to 
&gt; execute as many tests as possible.

I don&#39;t know if this already exists but it could be interesting to develop a
recorder/player wrapper mock object.  You can set up the mock object to save
into a file the response it receives via the wrapped object.  You can then
reset the mock object to replay (without the wrapped object) from a file.  If
this is done automatically, it can really be very handy to test databases.

I don&#39;t know if this is obvious but there&#39;s a simple way to share a connection
between multiple tests (if you don&#39;t have static variables) to speed up your
tests:

public void MyTestCase {

   public static Test suite() {
      return new TestSetup( new TestSuite(MyTestCase.class) {
         private Connection conn;
         setUp() {
            conn = new Connection(...);
            for ( int i = 0; i &lt; suite.countTestCases(); i++ ) {
               MyTestCase test = ( MyTestCase ) suite.testAt( i );
               test.setConnection(conn);
            }
         }
         tearDown() {
            conn.close();
         }
      };
   }

   Connection connection;

   public void setConnection(Connectio connection) {
      this.connection = connection;
   }

}

So you don&#39;t have to open/close a connection before/after each test.

